My husband (William) and I stopped by today around 7:15pm to try their food for the first time, and understandably there was a waitlist. We put our name down and patiently waited. We saw people come and go and that was fine, but when we started seeing other people that got there after us and were seated before us I immediately asked the male server how much longer It would be and he said we were almost next. I politely explained to him how come other people that got there after us were already being seated. He proceeded to say because the people were bigger groups. We would be next soon pointing at tables that seat 2 people. I’m like no that’s not right because if we have to wait, so do other people. First come first serve, right? I understand if it’s a party of 5 or more but people were in groups of 3 or more and it’s unfair if we got there first. We decided to take our names off the list and go eat somewhere else. I didn’t get his name but it’s a white male server or host with a tattoo sleeve. Very disappointing that we waited for more than 45 mins and ended up having to leave because of the bad service we received. I definitely do not recommend this place.

When I arrived here with my boyfriend for a bite to eat, it had been our second time being there. We got in after being carded due to it being a bar as well. It wasn’t filled much but as soon as our waitress came by she said “what do you want” rude, while rolling her eyes. We were thrown back but we assumed she’s just having a rough day so we let that go as we ordered a beer for ourselves. As she came back with our beers she tossed them on the table and walked away as they spilled over the table. It made us want to leave right away. The food and how good we knew it was made us stay. We had been ready to order but she had left once dropping off our beers at the table. I was hungry and my boyfriend lifted his hand in search for her. She came over not even looking at us and said “mhm what do you want” my boyfriend was getting irritated and firmly ordered for both of us. She wasn’t much older than me, and was about my boyfriends age and was acting like a high school girl. As we ate she rarely came check on us and we noticed her kindness to every other table. Realizing I look young, we came to the conclusion she acted this way due to thinking I was underage. As we left, (leaving no tip due to how bad service was) I got a horrible dirty look from another waitress sitting at the bar table leaning back and my boyfriend softly under his breath said “that’s ridiculous” because he even noticed. I have never been treated with such disrespect at a restaurant/bar in my whole life. The only reason I will go there again is for the food because I absolutely love it. Hope this never happens to anyone else or me ever again.
